The paper deals with metric learning and kernel methods, which are commonly used in machine learning and computer vision applications. The use of relative-distance constraints is also relevant to semi-supervised learning, which is a common topic in the sub-categories of machine learning (cs.LG), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI).
